==English==

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ælən|-ælən]]

===Proper noun===
'''Alan'''

#A male [[given name]].

===Etymology===

Celtic name or an early Irish name, perhaps connected with ''ail'', 'noble'. It may have been the name of a Celtic deity, the brother of ''Bran''. Welsh ''Alawn'', 'harmony'. 'Member of the tribe the Alans'.

